---
import DocLayout from "../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
import AegisLogo from "../components/AegisLogo.astro";
---

<DocLayout title="Home" description="The AEGIS Initiative — governance-first AI security. Capability without constraint is not intelligence.">
  <div class="hero">
    <AegisLogo size={96} />
    <h1>AEGIS Initiative</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Capability without constraint is not intelligence&trade;</p>
  </div>

  <hr />

  <section class="mission">
    <h2>Mission</h2>
    <p>
      The AEGIS Initiative exists to establish governance-first security as the
      foundational standard for autonomous AI systems. We develop enforceable
      governance frameworks, publish open specifications, and engage with
      policymakers and standards bodies to ensure that AI capability is always
      bounded by constitutional constraint.
    </p>
    <p>
      AEGIS™ is not anti-AI. AEGIS™ is pro-governance. We believe the path to
      trustworthy AI runs through deterministic enforcement, transparent audit
      trails, and human oversight that cannot be bypassed by the systems it
      governs.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Current Focus</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://aegis-constitution.com">AEGIS Constitution</a> published — versioned, citeable governance charter for AI systems</li>
      <li>4 papers submitted: IEEE Computer, IEEE Data Descriptions, NIST AI RMF position statement, NCCoE AI Agent Identity &amp; Access Management</li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-core">aegis-core</a> v0.1.2 stable — governance enforcement engine with 403 tests</li>
      <li><a href="https://aegis-governance.com">ATX-1 v2.1</a> threat matrix published — 10 tactics, 29 techniques for agentic AI threat modeling</li>
      <li><a href="https://aegis-docs.com">aegis-docs.com</a>, <a href="https://aegis-governance.com">aegis-governance.com</a>, and <a href="https://aegis-federation.com">aegis-federation.com</a> all live</li>
      <li>Federation protocol (<a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-federation">RFC-0016</a>) drafted — cross-domain machine discovery for AI governance</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="nav-cards">
    <h2>Explore</h2>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <a href="/about/" class="card">
        <h3>About</h3>
        <p>What AEGIS™ is, how we work, and the three-layer architecture behind it.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/constitution/" class="card">
        <h3>Constitution</h3>
        <p>The canonical governance charter — versioned, citeable, openly licensed.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/policy/" class="card">
        <h3>Policy &amp; Research</h3>
        <p>Published papers, NIST submissions, and policy engagement.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/press/" class="card">
        <h3>Press</h3>
        <p>Press releases, published articles, and media resources.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/contact/" class="card">
        <h3>Contact</h3>
        <p>Reach out for press inquiries, policy engagement, or general questions.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 2.75rem;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .tagline {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Sans", system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .mission {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .card-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .card-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 960px) {
    .card-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .card {
    display: block;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--color-text);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-subtle);
    transition: border-color 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
  }

  .card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
</style>
